race.description: Property For Doctors Fillies & Mares Maiden Plate
race.comment: GOOD HARMONY (9) was well in commission last start over 1600m at Pakenham when fourth, beaten 5 lengths. Found only one better the start prior and looks to have the best form. KENTUCKY WOMEN (2) showed good early muster and fought on to finish second last start over 1200m at Dunkeld. In a suitable race and can find the winner's circle. MISLIGHT (3) was in the money two starts back at Mornington but was unable to repeat the effort last time when ninth, beaten 53 lengths, at Pakenham over 1600m. This is a nice drop in grade. REEL CRYSTAL (10) turned in an eye-catching run over 1472m at Kyneton last time, ridden back before coming home with a powerful run to finish third. Will spot them a start but watch for her late. IMMORTAL MATILDA (14) hasn't done much to inspire confidence to this point, but will find this easier than most races she's contested and gets weight off all rivals after the 4kg claim for an in-form rider.
